1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA ยง1825-B, sub-ยง15 is enacted to read:
3 15. Records. The Director of the Bureau of General Services shall preserve and make
4 available on a publicly accessible website all records and documents regarding the
5 competitive bidding process, including a notice of intent to waive competitive bidding
6 under subsection 2 and all underlying supporting documents and all requests for proposals
7 and all underlying supporting documents, including responses, accepted responses and any
8 related financial agreements, and may not delete or destroy any records, correspondence or
9 financial agreements related to the procurement of goods or services except as required by
10 law.
11 Sec. 2. Record recovery. The Department of Administrative and Financial Services
12 shall to the extent possible recover and publish on a publicly accessible website all past
13 notices of intent to waive the competitive bidding process and all underlying supporting
14 documents.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This bill requires the Director of the Bureau of General Services within the Department
1177 of Administrative and Financial Services to preserve and make available on a publicly
1188 accessible website all records and documents related to the competitive bidding process,
1199 including notices of intent to waive competitive bidding. This bill also directs the
2200 department to recover and publish past notices of intent to waive competitive bidding.
